Name.creator: Nin, Anaïs, 1903-1977
Title: Diary 1, 1914 July 25-1915 May 19.
Description.note: Holograph. In dark blue/black/grey/silver marbled boards with dark blue half leather binding. With photographs, notes, drawings and ephemera laid in the diary.

Name.creator: Nin, Anaïs, 1903-1977
Title: Diary 62. Kenilworth & Death of the Mother. Mon Journal, 1939 October-1940 November.
Description.note: Holograph. Bound in red cloth. pp.1-[654].  Letters in envelopes are tipped in following unnumbered pages.Photos of Caresse Crosby, Henry Miller, Salvador Dali, the Earl of Kenilworth, AN with Mr. & Mrs. Ruttner, Jimmy Sternes. “Diacritical & historical materialism,” pp.1-21. With letters from Henry Miller, John, the Earl of Kenilworth, Hugo, postcards, pocket calendar, clippings. With programs forperformances for the Katherine Dunham Dance Group and Joaquin Nin-Culmell. Catalog card for Winter of Artifice tipped in verso of front cover.
